Exception→ An event that disrupts normal flow of execution.
try→ Block of code where exception might occur.
catch→ Block to handle the exception.
finally→ Block that always executes, whether exception occurs or not.
throw→ Used to explicitly throw an exception.
throws→ Declares exceptions a method might throw.

ArithmeticException → division by zero
NullPointerException → using null object
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException → invalid array index
NumberFormatException → invalid number parsing
IOException → input/output errors

NoSuchElementException→ 	Element not found on the page
ElementNotVisibleException→ Element exists but not visible
TimeoutException→ Wait condition not met in time
StaleElementReferenceException→ 	Element is no longer attached to DOM
WebDriverException→ General WebDriver failure
